1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Did you know that WordPress offers a diagnosis of your site health?

2
00:00:04,680 --> 00:00:07,680
In this session we are going to explore how to ensure you keep your site in tip-top shape.

3
00:00:11,240 --> 00:00:14,240
The site health widget can be found on the Dashboard or you can make your way to Tools

4
00:00:16,980 --> 00:00:19,980
and click on Site Hhealth.

5
00:00:20,340 --> 00:00:23,340
And as you will notice at the top, my site health needs to be improved.

6
00:00:24,900 --> 00:00:27,900
There are two tabs on the site health page, status and info.

7
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:34,700
The status tab allows you to see critical information about your WordPress configuration,

8
00:00:36,980 --> 00:00:39,980
along with anything else that requires your attention.

9
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:44,300
The info tab is a granular view of the technical aspects of your WordPress website.

10
00:00:48,820 --> 00:00:51,820
You can see detailed information about every aspect of your site, such as themes, plugins,

11
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:59,900
and your server setup for example.

12
00:01:03,380 --> 00:01:06,380
There is also a useful export feature that allows you to copy all the information about

13
00:01:08,260 --> 00:01:11,260
your site to the clipboard.

14
00:01:10,500 --> 00:01:13,500
When we go back to the status tab, you will notice the two main categories are security

15
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:18,500
or performance related issues.

16
00:01:18,740 --> 00:01:21,740
Critical issues refer to parts of your website that can be potential security vulnerabilities

17
00:01:23,940 --> 00:01:26,940
or serious performance issues.

18
00:01:26,260 --> 00:01:29,260
The critical issue coming up for me at the moment is that my site is running an outdated

19
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,100
version of PHP.

20
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:37,700
As the PHP version is set at the server level by your hosting company, updating involves

21
00:01:40,340 --> 00:01:43,340
either going to your host's Dashboard and changing the settings there or if that's not an option

22
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:51,100
asking them to do it.

23
00:01:50,180 --> 00:01:53,180
Please remember to back up your site before updating WordPress or the PHP version you

24
00:01:55,340 --> 00:01:58,340
are using.

25
00:01:57,140 --> 00:02:00,140
Other types of critical issues you may encounter are one or more required modules are missing.

26
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:05,580
You have plugins waiting to be updated.

27
00:02:05,220 --> 00:02:08,220
Your site could not complete a loopback request etc.

28
00:02:08,940 --> 00:02:11,940
When you open the accordion, you will learn more about which steps to take to solve a

29
00:02:13,180 --> 00:02:16,180
specific problem.

30
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:18,900
Next we can talk about recommended improvements.

31
00:02:18,780 --> 00:02:21,780
This section lists all the items that are not critical for your website but should be

32
00:02:23,580 --> 00:02:26,580
modified for better security and performance.

33
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:30,060
In my case, I should first update the version of WordPress that I am using and then remove

34
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:34,860
any inactive plugins and themes.

35
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:38,300
To update WordPress, you can click on Please update now at the top of the page and this

36
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:42,860
will take you to updates.

37
00:02:42,820 --> 00:02:45,820
Now you can merely click on Update to the new version and remember to back up your database

38
00:02:47,620 --> 00:02:50,620
and files.

39
00:02:50,140 --> 00:02:53,140
To remove an inactive theme, make your way to Appearance, open up the inactive theme

40
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:02,220
and click on Delete bottom right.

41
00:03:04,580 --> 00:03:07,580
Now we will move on to inactive plugins.

42
00:03:07,780 --> 00:03:10,780
Make your way to plugins and this time we can use the bulk select option by selecting

43
00:03:14,060 --> 00:03:17,060
all the inactive plugins and deleting them simultaneously.

44
00:03:21,140 --> 00:03:24,140
Let's make our way back to the Site Hhealth page as there is one more recommended improvement

45
00:03:26,020 --> 00:03:29,020
that we need to discuss.

46
00:03:28,940 --> 00:03:31,940
The last recommended improvement is suggesting that I install two optional PHP modules

47
00:03:34,860 --> 00:03:37,860
that have not been installed.

48
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:40,100
You could install these in CPanel, Plesk or similar software if your web host provides

49
00:03:42,420 --> 00:03:45,420
that access.

50
00:03:43,420 --> 00:03:46,420
But if your hosting company has not provided you with a way to install these yourself,

51
00:03:47,940 --> 00:03:50,940
you can contact your host and ask them to do it for you.

52
00:03:51,860 --> 00:03:54,860
Lastly, the tests that have been passed are all the other items that are tested by the

53
00:03:57,220 --> 00:04:00,220
site health tool and shows no issues.

54
00:04:01,260 --> 00:04:04,260
You can learn more about this tool when you go to the site health support page.

55
00:04:06,740 --> 00:04:09,740
Remember, Lee Hunt said, "The groundwork for all happiness, is good health."

